Bounty Day!
Mark Zuckerberg was invited
Come celebrate Bounty Day (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bounty_Day) as well as other awesome things that happened on January 23d. Things like: The war elephant corps of the Southern Han being soundly defeated at Shao by crossbow fire from Song Dynasty troops. The death of Elva Zona Heaster in Greenbrier County, West Virginia that resulted in the only US court case where the testimony of a ghost helped secure a conviction. The sale of a flying disc to the Wham-O toy company, later renamed to the "Frisbee". The birth of David Braginsky, me. So come by and celebrate everything that makes life wonderful (hint: it's you). I will have snacks, but feel free (and not obligated) to bring more things to share. (If I missed you in the invites, you are extra-invited)
